          <h3>Why Use Semantic HTML?</h3>
          <p>Semantic HTML helps search engines and screen readers understand the structure and meaning of your content. Tags like <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> make your site more accessible and SEO-friendly.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3>Introduction to Accessibility</h3>
          <p>Accessibility ensures your site is usable by everyone, including people with disabilities. Use alt text for images, clear heading structures, and ARIA roles when needed.</p>
        </article>
